@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - streaming/Stream
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
state "SyncSecret" as sync_secret
state "SecretBlocked" as secret_blocked
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : CreateStream
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE
observe --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\ncompartment_id,\ndefined_tags, freeform_tags\n(+1 more)
apply_update --> sync_secret : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> sync_secret : apply secret policy\nready-only writes after\nACTIVE
sync_secret --> secret_blocked : Secret sync fails
secret_blocked --> sync_secret : retry Secret sync
sync_secret --> ready : Secret side effects succeed
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Legacy-adapter controllers map
provider states into the shared controller
phases while open gaps keep additional
transitions explicit.
service: streaming
slug: stream
kind: Stream
archetype: legacy-adapter
status/finalizer: manual / none
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: compartment_id, defined_tags,
freeform_tags, stream_pool_id
reject before mutate: force-new fields name,
partitions, retention_in_hours and conflicts
compartment_id -> stream_pool_id, stream_pool_id
-> compartment_id
list lookup: oci_streaming_streams filters
compartment_id, id, name, state (+1 more)
conflicts: compartment_id -> stream_pool_id,
stream_pool_id -> compartment_id
open gaps: bind-versus-create,
delete-confirmation, endpoint-materialization,
legacy-adapter, list-lookup (+2 more)
Create or bind selection depends on name-based
list lookup with optional pool and compartment
filters.
Endpoint secret materialization happens only
after ACTIVE.
Delete is best-effort today; DELETING is treated
as sufficient for cleanup and finalizer removal.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: best-effort
delete observe: GetStream or ListStreams
delete targets: DELETED
Secret cleanup waits for OCI delete
confirmation.
end note
@enduml
